result.execSummary:
The defendant Nattali D Guynn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly conduct - domestic. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:30 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Defendant Nattali D Guynn in court.  State Public Defender's Office Law Intern appeared for the defense by Eric Schleuter.  Prosecuting attorney Andrea M Will in court for the State of Wisconsin. Prosecuting attorney moves to amend Count 1 to Disorderly Conduct contrary to ordinance 13-102(c)(8), Wisconsin Statutes/Waukesha County Ordinances. Court approves amendment. Mr. Schleuter enters a no contest plea on behalf of his client to the Amended Count 1.  Court accepts the plea and will find the defendant guilty of the Amended Count 1.  Court also orders Count 2 be dismissed and read in.

COUNT 1:
 The Court Orders the Following:	

$367.50 (includes DV surcharge) to be paid at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing 11/01/2022. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 27, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Plea/sentencing hearing on August 29, 2022 at 09:30 am.

Kees provides an update, she is requesting a plea and sentencing date in about 60-90 days to allow time for defendant to complete upfront treatment.  Court adjourns for plea and sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 09:30 am.
